===Verb===
{{en-verb|hears|hearing|heard}}

# {{lb|en|intransitive|stative}} To [[perceive]] sounds through the [[ear]]. {{defdate|from 10th c.}}
#: {{ux|en|I was deaf, and now I can '''hear'''.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|stative}} To [[perceive]] (a sound, or something producing a sound) with the [[ear]], to [[recognize]] (something) in an auditory way. {{defdate|from 10th c.}}
#: {{ux|en|I '''heard''' a sound from outside the window.}}
#* {{RQ:Churchill Celebrity|chapter=4|passage=Mr. Cooke at once began a tirade against the residents of Asquith for permitting a sandy and generally disgraceful condition of the roads. So roundly did he vituperate the inn management in particular, and with such a loud flow of words, that I trembled lest he should be '''heard''' on the veranda.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To exercise this faculty [[intentionally]]; to [[listen]] to. {{defdate|from 10th c.}}
#* '''1526''', {{w|William Tyndale}}, trans. ''Bible'', {{w|Gospel of John|John}} X:
#*: Agayne there was dissencion amonge the iewes for these sayinges, and many of them sayd: He hath the devyll, and is madde: why '''heare''' ye hym?
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1935|author=[https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/288354.George_Goodchild George Goodchild]| title=Death on the Centre Court| chapter=3| passage=It had been his intention to go to Wimbledon, but as he himself said: “Why be blooming well frizzled when you can '''hear''' all the results over the wireless. And results are all that concern me.&nbsp;[&hellip;]”}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To listen favourably to; to [[grant]] (a request etc.). {{defdate|from 10th c.}}
#: {{ux|en|Eventually the king chose to '''hear''' her entreaties.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To receive information about; to come to [[learn]] of. {{defdate|from 10th c.}}
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1667|author={{w|John Milton}}|title={{w|Paradise Lost}}|passage=Adam, soon as he '''heard''' / The fatal Trespass don by Eve, amaz'd, / Astonied stood and Blank {{...}} }}
# {{lb|en|with ''from''}} To be [[contact]]ed by.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2009 |title=The Pearl Within  |author= Elsa T. Aguries |page=141 |ISBN=1615796657 |passage=When I don't '''hear''' from you, My days feel long and lonely. }}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2012|title=From the Depths of Evil |author=Art Wiederhold & Charles Sutphen |page=343 |ISBN=1466922532 |passage=They're ten hours overdue. Have you '''heard''' from any of them since they left Nineveh? }}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2012 |title=A Mission from God: A Memoir and Challenge for America |author=James Meredith |ISBN=1451674740 |passage=She left and I never '''heard''' from her again.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[listen]] to (a person, case) in a court of law; to [[try]]. {{defdate|from 12th c.}}
#: {{ux|en|Your case will be '''heard''' at the end of the month.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|informal}} To [[sympathize]] with; to understand the feelings or opinion of.
#: {{ux|en|You're tired of all the ads on TV? I '''hear''' ya.}}

